Surprising... Disconcerting... See confusing... Stumbled upon it by chance, I wasn't expecting that. At the side of the road, surrounded by tall trees, it seems very small.  But how does this represent Johnny Hallyday? He was a Face, a Voice of French song.  And there, for some, it looks like the entrance to a scrapyard or a motorcycle dealership. For my part, I see the sign of a restaurant/dance bar like Jack Rabbit Slim's in Pulp Fiction but in a biker version.  In short, it's contemporary art we'll say... Everyone is free to see what they want ;-)  But obviously, few see Johnny there, it's a shame all the same....
